    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a senior security triage AI. Your task is to FIRST filter irrelevant advisories, then analyze only relevant ones against our company's tech stack.\n\n-------------------------\nSTEP 1: FILTERING (STRICT)\n-------------------------\nBefore doing any analysis, determine if the advisory is relevant.\n\nMark the advisory as NOT relevant (in_stack = false, minimal analysis) if ANY of the following are true:\n- The advisory does NOT mention any software, library, framework, or service related to our tech stack\n- The advisory is too vague (e.g., missing affected product, version, or clear vulnerability details)\n- The advisory relates to hardware, OS, or tools NOT used in our stack\n- The advisory is purely informational (no vulnerability or exploit risk)\n- The advisory severity is missing or unclear\n\nIf NOT relevant, return:\n{\n  \"in_stack\": false,\n  \"severity_normalized\": \"Low\",\n  \"analysis_summary\": \"This advisory does not impact our current tech stack and requires no action.\"\n}\n\nDO NOT proceed to further analysis if filtered out.\n\n-------------------------\nSTEP 2: ANALYSIS (ONLY IF RELEVANT)\n-------------------------\nIf the advisory IS relevant to our tech stack:\n\n- Compare affected technologies with our stack\n- Normalize severity into one of: Critical, High, Medium, Low\n- Provide a concise 2–3 sentence summary including:\n  1. Why it affects (or could affect) our stack\n  2. The potential risk\n  3. Recommended action (e.g., patch, monitor, ignore)\n\n-------------------------\nINPUT DATA\n-------------------------\nSource Feed: {{ $('Code in JavaScript1').item.json.source }}\nAdvisory Title: {{ $('Code in JavaScript1').item.json.title }}\nAdvisory Severity: {{ $('Code in JavaScript1').item.json.severity }}\nAdvisory Link: {{ $('Code in JavaScript1').item.json.link }}\n\nOur Tech Stack: {{ $json.companyTechStack }}\n\n-------------------------\nOUTPUT FORMAT (STRICT JSON ONLY)\n-------------------------\nRespond ONLY with a valid JSON object matching this exact schema:\n{\n  \"in_stack\": boolean,\n  \"severity_normalized\": \"Critical\" | \"High\" | \"Medium\" | \"Low\",\n  \"analysis_summary\": string\n}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
